<body>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 1: COVER -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="cover-page">
    <h1>VibeFlow</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 14pt; color: #4f46e5; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 5pt; margin-bottom: 30pt;">
      Employee Request Approval System
    </p>
    <div style="width: 80pt; height: 3pt; background-color: #10b981; margin: 0 auto 40pt auto;"></div>
    
    <div class="meta-box">
      <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Project Name:</span><span>VibeFlow Approval System</span></div>
      <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Assessment:</span><span>Vibe Coder / Rapid Prototyper Suite</span></div>
      <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Tech Stack:</span><span>Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Supabase, Vercel</span></div>
      <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Developer:</span><span>Antigravity AI Engineer (Google DeepMind)</span></div>
      <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Date:</span><span>July 2026</span></div>
      <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Status:</span><span style="color: #10b981; font-weight: bold;">Production-Ready & Fully Deployed</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 2: PROBLEM STATEMENT -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>1. Problem Statement</h2>
    <p>In modern high-speed businesses, operational delay in reviewing and approving internal request folders—such as annual leaves, equipment procurement, software licenses, budget allocations, and travel arrangements—causes significant organizational friction. Common bottlenecks include:</p>
    
    <h3>Friction and Delays</h3>
    <p>Relying on legacy channels like email threads or spreadsheets often leads to misplaced files, double-bookings, and untracked communication logs.</p>
    
    <h3>Information Asymmetry</h3>
    <p>Employees have no centralized panel to view request progress, track audit histories, or review feedback justification comments from reviewers.</p>
    
    <h3>Data Security Vulnerabilities</h3>
    <p>Without secure database authorization, sensitive personnel details (like salary budgets or medical leave reasons) are exposed to unauthorized viewing.</p>
    
    <h3>Reporting Deficiencies</h3>
    <p>Managers lack analytical overview metrics and search filters to quickly analyze request volumes or export tabular reports for audits.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 3: SOLUTION OVERVIEW -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>2. Solution Overview</h2>
    <p>VibeFlow addresses these challenges with a centralized SaaS platform featuring distinct role-based views, strict form validation, storage integration, and real-time dashboard syncs.</p>
    
    <h3>Unified Request Lifecycle</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Employee Submissions:</strong> Employees compile requests choosing specific categories and priorities, attach supporting documentation, and submit. The item is logged as "Pending".</li>
      <li><strong>Manager Notification:</strong> The record instantly appears in the Manager's dashboard queue.</li>
      <li><strong>Evaluation:</strong> Managers review details, download attachments, select "Approve" or "Reject", add comments, and submit.</li>
      <li><strong>Websocket Sync:</strong> Real-time subscriptions push the status update to the employee's screen instantly without requiring page reloads.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Core Advantages</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Enforced Verification:</strong> Form fields validate dynamically using Zod before submissions.</li>
      <li><strong>Secured Access:</strong> Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) restricts access so users only see authorized data rows.</li>
      <li><strong>Exportable Audits:</strong> Managers can instantly export the filtered queue into clean CSV sheets.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 4: TECH STACK -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>3. Technology Stack</h2>
    <p>The application is engineered using a robust, modern, single-language stack optimized for speed, scalability, and ease of deployment:</p>
    
    <h3>Next.js 15 (App Router)</h3>
    <p>Utilized for type-safe routing layouts, React Server Components (RSC) to reduce client load, and Server Actions to securely process database mutations.</p>
    
    <h3>TypeScript</h3>
    <p>Provides strict static compilation checking across database queries, Zod validation schemas, and client components.</p>
    
    <h3>Tailwind CSS v4</h3>
    <p>Powers responsive layout design tokens, custom color schemes, glassmorphic containers, and transition animations.</p>
    
    <h3>Supabase (Backend-as-a-Service)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>PostgreSQL Database:</strong> Hosts relational schemas and handles automated profiles syncing via trigger functions.</li>
      <li><strong>Supabase Auth:</strong> Manages secure email/password credential sessions.</li>
      <li><strong>Storage Buckets:</strong> Holds file attachments with bucket-level security.</li>
      <li><strong>Real-time Engines:</strong> Broadcasters database mutations via websockets.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Vercel</h3>
    <p>Edge hosting platform synced to GitHub pipelines for automated builds and deployment.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 5: SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>4. System Architecture</h2>
    <p>VibeFlow implements a clean, decoupled architectural flow ensuring proper separation of concerns:</p>
    
    <div class="code-block">
  [Browser Client Component Views] 
           │
           ▼ (Zod Client Form Validation)
  [Supabase Storage Bucket API] <── (Optional Files Upload Direct)
           │
           ▼ (Invoke Async Server Actions / API Handlers)
  [Next.js Server-Side Context] (await cookies / auth.getUser)
           │
           ▼ (Enforce PostgreSQL Row Level Security Rules)
  [Supabase DB / Profiles & Requests Tables] ──┐
           ▲                                   │ (Trigger DB Event)
           │                                   ▼
  [Websocket Real-time Subscription] ◄─────────┘
    </div>

    <h3>Architectural Highlights</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Client Validation:</strong> Intercepts invalid inputs before triggering server requests.</li>
      <li><strong>Direct Storage Uploads:</strong> Clients upload files directly to Supabase storage to bypass server buffering, saving the resulting URL.</li>
      <li><strong>Token Refreshing Middleware:</strong> Intercepts page requests to refresh auth sessions and enforce dashboard path protection.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 6: DATABASE DESIGN -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>5. Database Design & Schemas</h2>
    <p>The database schema resides under the `public` schema of PostgreSQL, consisting of two primary tables with a one-to-many relationship:</p>
    
    <div class="code-block">
  [Profiles Table]
  - id (UUID, Primary Key, references auth.users)
  - full_name (TEXT, not null)
  - email (TEXT, not null)
  - role (TEXT, check constraint: 'employee' | 'manager')
  - created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
         │
         └─── (1-to-Many Relationship) ───┐
                                          ▼
                                   [Requests Table]
                                   - id (UUID, PK)
                                   - employee_id (UUID, FK -> profiles.id)
                                   - title / description (TEXT)
                                   - category / priority (TEXT)
                                   - start_date / end_date (DATE)
                                   - attachment_url (TEXT, nullable)
                                   - status (TEXT, default 'Pending')
                                   - manager_comment (TEXT, nullable)
                                   - created_at / updated_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
    </div>

    <h3>Automated Profile Triggers</h3>
    <p>An Auth Trigger function `handle_new_user()` listens to inserts in `auth.users` (created during signUp) and automatically mirrors the new user's metadata (full name and role) into `public.profiles` instantly.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 7: SYSTEM FEATURES -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>6. Application Features</h2>
    
    <h3>Employee Operations Portal</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Create Requests:</strong> Validated forms with date-range checks and files upload support.</li>
      <li><strong>Edit Pending:</strong> Modify title, description, category, priority, or replace attachment files for any requests still marked as "Pending".</li>
      <li><strong>Delete Pending:</strong> Remove a pending request completely.</li>
      <li><strong>Timeline Tracking:</strong> Interactive history trail detailing approval updates and manager feedback.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Manager Control Center</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Queue Overview:</strong> High-level metrics showing Total, Pending, Approved, and Rejected counts.</li>
      <li><strong>Filters Panel:</strong> Inline queries, category dropdowns, and status indicators.</li>
      <li><strong>Decision Modals:</strong> Single-click Approve/Reject panels requiring review comments.</li>
      <li><strong>CSV Generation:</strong> Generates formatted CSV sheets of the currently filtered dataset.</li>
      <li><strong>Interactive Sorting:</strong> Toggle-sort rows by employee name, category, priority, and date.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 8: APPLICATION INTERFACE WIREFRAMES -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>7. User Interface Mockups & Layouts</h2>
    <p>Below are structural wireframe mockups representing the application's core views:</p>
    
    <h3>Responsive Dashboard Shell Layout</h3>
    <div class="code-block">
+--------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
| VibeFlow Logo            | NAVBAR: Hamburger Toggle | Page Title | User Initials |
| User Profile Initials    +-------------------------------------------------------+
|                          | MAIN WORKSPACE CONTENT PANEL                          |
| - Dashboard link         |                                                       |
| - Profile Settings link  |  [Stats Cards: Total | Pending | Approved | Rejected] |
| - Sign Out button        |                                                       |
|                          |  [Search Input] [Category Filter] [Status Filter]     |
|                          |                                                       |
|                          |  [Requests Data Table Listing / Status Badges]        |
+--------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
    </div>

    <h3>Timeline Audit Log Interface</h3>
    <div class="code-block">
(*) Request Submitted -------> Logged on: July 9, 2026 at 12:30 PM
 |                             (Timestamp recorded automatically)
 |
(*) Reviewed by Manager ----> Approved on: July 9, 2026 at 1:45 PM
                               "Approved. Coordinate with finance to process."
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 9: DEMO & TEST ACCOUNTS -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>8. Demo Setup & Credentials</h2>
    <p>To audit the live prototype, deploy the code to Vercel, complete the database setup, and use the demo credentials:</p>
    
    <h3>Environment Variables Required</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>`NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`</li>
      <li>`NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`</li>
      <li>`SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Pre-seeded Credentials</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>User Role</th>
          <th>Login Email Address</th>
          <th>Account Password</th>
          <th>Available Privileges</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Manager</strong></td>
          <td>manager@test.com</td>
          <td>Password123</td>
          <td>Full approvals, dashboard statistics cards, CSV export, column sorting.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Employee</strong></td>
          <td>employee@test.com</td>
          <td>Password123</td>
          <td>Submit requests, upload attachments, edit/delete pending items, view timeline logs.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p><em>Note: You can skip typing credentials by clicking the <strong>"Quick Login"</strong> button panels on the landing page once the database has been seeded.</em></p>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <!-- PAGE 10: CONCLUSION & ROADMAP -->
  <!-- ========================================== -->
  <div class="page">
    <h2>9. Conclusion & Future Roadmap</h2>
    <p>VibeFlow demonstrates a secure, high-performance, and responsive request approval prototype. With more development time, the following features would be added to the roadmap:</p>
    
    <h3>Multi-Stage Approval Workflows</h3>
    <p>Enable sequential routing of request folders through multiple authorization tiers (e.g., Department Lead -> HR Manager -> CFO approval for high budgets).</p>
    
    <h3>Email Notifications</h3>
    <p>Integrate Resend or SendGrid APIs to dispatch automated notification emails to employees as soon as their request status changes.</p>
    
    <h3>Visual Analytics & Charts</h3>
    <p>Incorporate interactive bar charts and pie graphs (using libraries like Recharts) inside the Manager panel to show category distributions and SLA review time trends.</p>
    
    <h3>Automated SLA Alert Warnings</h3>
    <p>Trigger automated warning notifications on the dashboard if a request remains in a "Pending" status for more than 48 hours without a decision.</p>
  </div>

</body>
